results.name: a(1)=2^3*5*7*29=8120; for n>1, a(n) = (-1)sigma(a(n-1)).
comment: (-1)sigma is defined in A049060. This is a cyclic sequence whose period is 8, so these numbers are called "(-1)sigma sociable numbers of order 8".
